# Agent Safety Doctrine (MA-14)

Canonical: [META_ARCHITECT_LAWBOOK.md](../../META_ARCHITECT_LAWBOOK.md) Doctrine XIV; companion [docs/governance/AGENT_SAFETY_DOCTRINE.md](../../docs/governance/AGENT_SAFETY_DOCTRINE.md)

Coding agents are **builders**, not architects.

## MUST NOT

- Rewrite architecture without blueprint approval
- Merge constitutional / blueprint / contract changes without explicit human acceptance
- Bypass governance gates, manifests, or proof requirements
- Treat CI green as permission to violate law
- Expand scope autonomously when uncertainty is high

## MAY

- Implement approved specs and contracts
- Add tests, receipts, and trust-bundle evidence
- Propose diffs and manifests for human review

## Governed-change manifest

When touching law, `docs/contracts/**`, `docs/governance/**`, `.cursor/rules/**`, or agent-safety CI: add or update a manifest under `governance/agent_change_manifests/` and run `make agent-safety-doctrine-gate`.

## Uncertainty

When uncertain, **hold or degrade** per [SWARM_LAW.md](../../docs/contracts/SWARM_LAW.md). Surface questions; do not improvise with high confidence.
